13:22.208 --> 13:24.625
in the passage except this.

13:27.208 --> 13:30.500
"When comes the beauty

13:27.208 --> 13:30.500
from Caribee,

13:30.500 --> 13:32.583
"she spends her time

13:30.500 --> 13:32.583
in Port of Spain,

13:32.583 --> 13:35.166
"watching foul flies

13:32.583 --> 13:35.166
roost in the spice tree

13:35.166 --> 13:39.166
under which Sir Chadwick prays

13:35.166 --> 13:39.166
on bended knee."

13:39.166 --> 13:43.583
What the hell does that mean?

13:39.166 --> 13:43.583
Uh... a Caribbean nursery

13:39.166 --> 13:43.583
rhyme? Or a riddle.

13:43.583 --> 13:45.083
(phone ringing)

13:43.583 --> 13:45.083
Or...

13:45.083 --> 13:46.583
perhaps a cipher hidden within.

13:46.583 --> 13:48.541
Agent Mills here.

13:48.541 --> 13:50.125
REYNOLDS:

13:48.541 --> 13:50.125
Abs, we got a second

13:48.541 --> 13:50.125
suspicious death.

13:50.125 --> 13:51.583
Head of the PTA killed

13:50.125 --> 13:51.583
inside her kitchen.

13:51.583 --> 13:54.250
I need you over here

13:51.583 --> 13:54.250
right away.

13:51.583 --> 13:54.250
On my way.

13:54.250 --> 13:56.208
It seems the creature

13:54.250 --> 13:56.208
struck again.

13:56.208 --> 14:00.583
Figure out what this means.

13:56.208 --> 14:00.583
I'm gonna go check this out.

14:00.583 --> 14:02.458
REYNOLDS:

14:00.583 --> 14:02.458
Whatever happened

14:00.583 --> 14:02.458
to this woman

14:02.458 --> 14:03.916
is too damn similar

14:02.458 --> 14:03.916
to that judge.

14:03.916 --> 14:06.708
You think it's some kind of

14:06.708 --> 14:08.625
toxin or virus?

14:06.708 --> 14:08.625
That's for the lab coats.

14:08.625 --> 14:10.708
I have a call into CDC.

14:08.625 --> 14:10.708
Until then,

14:10.708 --> 14:12.625
we monitor

14:10.708 --> 14:12.625
the situation.

14:12.625 --> 14:15.125
And the fire?

14:12.625 --> 14:15.125
A book burning.

14:15.125 --> 14:16.625
She showed up

14:15.125 --> 14:16.625
to the library

14:16.625 --> 14:19.791
a few hours ago

14:16.625 --> 14:19.791
and checked out a stack.

14:19.791 --> 14:21.708
Orwell, Salinger, Vonnegut.

14:21.708 --> 14:24.750
Neighbors heard her ranting

14:21.708 --> 14:24.750
about the board of education's

14:24.750 --> 14:26.791
conspiracy

14:24.750 --> 14:26.791
to corrupt young minds.

14:26.791 --> 14:28.750
Full-scale paranoid episode.

14:28.750 --> 14:31.083
Stay with me on this, Mills.

14:28.750 --> 14:31.083
Another one pops up,

14:31.083 --> 14:33.625
it's gonna turn into a circus

14:31.083 --> 14:33.625
around here real quick.

14:33.625 --> 14:35.875
No way I'm losing

14:33.625 --> 14:35.875
control of this.

14:39.750 --> 14:42.125
(phone ringing)

14:42.125 --> 14:44.750
I assume

14:42.125 --> 14:44.750
this call does not bode well.

14:44.750 --> 14:47.166
Another victim--

14:44.750 --> 14:47.166
housewife, mid-30s,

14:47.166 --> 14:48.541
chairwoman of the PTA.

14:48.541 --> 14:50.541
Don't acronym, Lieutenant.

14:50.541 --> 14:52.333
"Parent Teacher Association."

14:52.333 --> 14:54.083
Hold on.

14:54.083 --> 14:55.750
There's a pattern here.

14:55.750 --> 14:57.625
She's an authority figure.

14:57.625 --> 14:59.375
Person in a position of power.

14:59.375 --> 15:01.208
As were the other victims.

15:01.208 --> 15:03.583
A judge, General Washington...

15:03.583 --> 15:05.333
So it stands to reason,

15:05.333 --> 15:07.750
if the Soucouyant is the queen

15:05.333 --> 15:07.750
of her swarm,

15:07.750 --> 15:09.208
that she would attack

15:07.750 --> 15:09.208
other leaders.

15:09.208 --> 15:11.500
People in the driver's seat.

15:11.500 --> 15:15.291
And look at me,

15:11.500 --> 15:15.291
profiling a bug. I got to go.

15:15.291 --> 15:18.666
On me, Agent Mills.

15:15.291 --> 15:18.666
Who were you on the phone with?

15:18.666 --> 15:21.875
My roommate.

15:18.666 --> 15:21.875
I need you focused

15:18.666 --> 15:21.875
on this case, Agent.

15:21.875 --> 15:23.083
Instead of letting

15:21.875 --> 15:23.083
your personal life

15:23.083 --> 15:24.541
hamper another investigation.

15:35.541 --> 15:36.958
Okay...

15:36.958 --> 15:38.416
(engine starts)

15:47.000 --> 15:48.625
(engine revving,

15:47.000 --> 15:48.625
tires screeching, horn honking)

15:52.666 --> 15:54.625
(tires squealing)

15:54.625 --> 15:57.166
(horn honking)

15:57.166 --> 15:58.791
(tires squealing)

15:58.791 --> 16:02.166
Is everything

15:58.791 --> 16:02.166
all right?

15:58.791 --> 16:02.166
You tell me.

16:04.625 --> 16:08.041
(tires squealing)

16:08.041 --> 16:09.833
(horn honking)

16:09.833 --> 16:12.125
Whoa! Where are we going?

16:12.125 --> 16:14.625
I want some answers.

16:12.125 --> 16:14.625
I'm not sure I understand.

16:14.625 --> 16:16.750
We have a dead judge,

16:16.750 --> 16:18.083
dead housewife,

16:16.750 --> 16:18.083
and a cause of death

16:18.083 --> 16:19.583
that doesn't make any sense.

16:19.583 --> 16:21.125
Cut the crap for once.

16:21.125 --> 16:22.875
Why don't you tell me

16:22.875 --> 16:24.375
what's really going on?

16:24.375 --> 16:25.666
What's your game

16:24.375 --> 16:25.666
with my Nevins case?

16:25.666 --> 16:27.083
I spoke to Jenny already.

16:27.083 --> 16:28.458
You sent her in

16:27.083 --> 16:28.458
there, didn't you?

16:28.458 --> 16:30.583
No. I told you,

16:30.583 --> 16:33.166
her thing didn't start anywhere

16:30.583 --> 16:33.166
near your investigation.

16:33.166 --> 16:35.625
You said a lot,

16:33.166 --> 16:35.625
but none of it adds up.

16:35.625 --> 16:37.875
How did Granger

16:35.625 --> 16:37.875
really die?

16:37.875 --> 16:40.291
Why are you using your sister

16:37.875 --> 16:40.291
to blow a hole

16:40.291 --> 16:41.958
in the biggest case

16:40.291 --> 16:41.958
of my career?

16:41.958 --> 16:43.666
And who is that damn Crane guy?

16:43.666 --> 16:45.916
He's no historical

16:43.666 --> 16:45.916
consultant.

16:45.916 --> 16:48.125
Look, I know

16:45.916 --> 16:48.125
you like to win, Abbie,

16:48.125 --> 16:50.875
but going behind my back,

16:48.125 --> 16:50.875
undermining my authority?

16:50.875 --> 16:52.750
(laughs)

16:52.750 --> 16:54.541
You want to take it all away,

16:52.750 --> 16:54.541
is that it?

16:54.541 --> 16:55.958
You want it all for yourself?

16:56.958 --> 16:58.666
Hmm?

16:58.666 --> 17:00.666
Danny...

17:02.416 --> 17:03.750
Danny, please

17:02.416 --> 17:03.750
listen to me.

17:02.416 --> 17:03.750
To what?

17:03.750 --> 17:05.708
More lies, more double-talk?

17:05.708 --> 17:07.333
You've been stung by something.

17:07.333 --> 17:08.666
I've seen it

17:07.333 --> 17:08.666
in the other victims.

17:08.666 --> 17:11.250
It's impairing your judgment.

17:16.750 --> 17:18.000
(gasps)

17:21.583 --> 17:23.625
(panting)

17:25.625 --> 17:27.208
Okay, fine.

17:27.208 --> 17:29.250
Who are you calling?

17:27.208 --> 17:29.250
You trying to play me?

17:29.250 --> 17:32.250
Reynolds.

17:29.250 --> 17:32.250
You think I'll go

17:29.250 --> 17:32.250
down without a fight?

17:36.583 --> 17:39.041
Damn it, Mills, get off of me!

17:39.041 --> 17:42.625
I am sorry, Danny.

17:42.625 --> 17:43.708
Gonna get you some help.

17:43.708 --> 17:46.000
(grunts)

17:43.708 --> 17:46.000
I promise.

17:46.000 --> 17:48.000
(groans)

17:49.583 --> 17:50.958
Well, I gave

17:49.583 --> 17:50.958
him a sedative.

17:50.958 --> 17:52.666
Should knock him

17:50.958 --> 17:52.666
out for a bit.

17:52.666 --> 17:55.375
What happened

17:52.666 --> 17:55.375
to him anyway?

17:52.666 --> 17:55.375
He was stung by

17:55.375 --> 17:57.375
a Trinidadian paranoia monster.

17:57.375 --> 18:00.333
Welcome to Sleepy Hollow.

17:57.375 --> 18:00.333
Mm.

18:00.333 --> 18:03.416
CRANE:

18:00.333 --> 18:03.416
Lieutenant, the entry in

18:00.333 --> 18:03.416
Grace Dixon's journal--

18:03.416 --> 18:05.166
'tis not a riddle

18:03.416 --> 18:05.166
nor a nursery rhyme.

18:05.166 --> 18:07.541
'Tis a ditty devised

18:05.166 --> 18:07.541
to have a double meaning.

18:07.541 --> 18:08.750
It's the Trini way.

18:08.750 --> 18:10.333
I was down there

18:08.750 --> 18:10.333
once for Carnival.

18:10.333 --> 18:12.125
It's all about the

18:10.333 --> 18:12.125
double entendre.

18:12.125 --> 18:14.625
Listen: "When comes

18:12.125 --> 18:14.625
the beauty from Caribee,

18:14.625 --> 18:17.625
she spends her time

18:14.625 --> 18:17.625
in Port of Spain."

18:17.625 --> 18:19.125
Not time as measured by a clock.

18:19.125 --> 18:22.416
The herb Spanish thyme. Next.

18:22.416 --> 18:25.666
"Watching foul flies roost

18:22.416 --> 18:25.666
in the spice tree."

18:25.666 --> 18:27.500
Not a foul scent, but a spice.

18:27.500 --> 18:29.833
Bird pepper.

18:27.500 --> 18:29.833
A list of ingredients.

18:29.833 --> 18:34.000
For the tonic Miss Dixon used to

18:29.833 --> 18:34.000
treat Washington. And finally:

18:34.000 --> 18:37.000
"Under which Sir Chadwick prays

18:34.000 --> 18:37.000
on bended knee."

18:37.000 --> 18:38.916
Chadon Beni-- a

18:37.000 --> 18:38.916
medicinal herb that only

18:38.916 --> 18:41.791
grows in Trinidad, but I know

18:38.916 --> 18:41.791
someone who may have a supply.

18:41.791 --> 18:43.666
You stay here with Reynolds.

18:43.666 --> 18:45.708
Joe and I will be back

18:43.666 --> 18:45.708
as soon as we can.

18:47.666 --> 18:49.791
Nice.

18:47.666 --> 18:49.791
Thank you.

18:49.791 --> 18:52.291
(reggae music playing low)

19:00.583 --> 19:02.708
(rings bell)

19:04.458 --> 19:06.708
♪ Wandering drummer messenger ♪

19:06.708 --> 19:08.041
♪ Om-pom, pom-pom-pom... ♪

19:08.041 --> 19:10.166
So I guess we put

19:08.041 --> 19:10.166
Abbie in a tight spot

19:10.166 --> 19:11.166
with the Nevins thing.

19:11.166 --> 19:13.166
She'll be all right.

19:13.166 --> 19:15.666
I know.

19:15.666 --> 19:18.333
Just, we were so close

19:15.666 --> 19:18.333
to finally getting some answers.

19:18.333 --> 19:20.625
I'm sorry, Joe.

19:20.625 --> 19:22.791
I wish there was

19:20.625 --> 19:22.791
another way.

19:20.625 --> 19:22.791
Hey, no. I mean,

19:22.791 --> 19:25.791
you went down that road

19:22.791 --> 19:25.791
as far as you could.

19:25.791 --> 19:27.666
Hope you know how much

19:25.791 --> 19:27.666
I appreciate it.

19:31.666 --> 19:33.291
So, what is this guy, some kind

19:33.291 --> 19:35.083
of Caribbean

19:33.291 --> 19:35.083
witch doctor, or...?

19:35.083 --> 19:36.541
MAN:

19:35.083 --> 19:36.541
Call me that again,

19:35.083 --> 19:36.541
and it's me and you.

19:36.541 --> 19:41.458
Jenny Mills. Long time.

19:41.458 --> 19:43.250
Long enough for you

19:41.458 --> 19:43.250
to get a man.

19:43.250 --> 19:45.291
Oh, no, he's not my...

19:43.250 --> 19:45.291
No, no, no, we're not...

19:45.291 --> 19:46.333
...boyfriend.

19:45.291 --> 19:46.333
...together.

19:46.333 --> 19:47.833
Irish moss.

19:47.833 --> 19:49.833
This'll give

19:47.833 --> 19:49.833
you stamina

19:49.833 --> 19:53.250
for those long,

19:49.833 --> 19:53.250
long nights, huh?

19:53.250 --> 19:54.500
(chuckling)

19:53.250 --> 19:54.500
Uh, we need something

19:54.500 --> 19:57.291
off the red list, Azzaca.

19:57.291 --> 19:59.750
Chadon Beni.

19:59.750 --> 20:02.083
That is a tough one

19:59.750 --> 20:02.083
on short notice.

20:02.083 --> 20:05.041
I have to call a fella

20:02.083 --> 20:05.041
who could call a fella

20:02.083 --> 20:05.041
who has a boat, but...

20:05.041 --> 20:07.416
No time to haggle.

20:05.041 --> 20:07.416
Quarter pound.

20:07.416 --> 20:08.708
Friends-and-family rate.

20:08.708 --> 20:10.958
We're on the clock.

20:10.958 --> 20:14.541
An Obeah man is only capable

20:10.958 --> 20:14.541
of so much, Jennifer Mills.

20:14.541 --> 20:16.166
I cannot bend time and space.

20:16.166 --> 20:17.333
And if we pay cash?

20:18.875 --> 20:22.541
Oh, you mean to say

20:18.875 --> 20:22.541
that  Chadon Beni?

20:23.583 --> 20:25.583
I have a pinch

20:23.583 --> 20:25.583
for emergencies.

20:25.583 --> 20:26.875
Oh. Yeah.

20:26.875 --> 20:28.916
I like this one.

20:28.916 --> 20:30.416
Keep him.

20:32.833 --> 20:34.750
(both chuckle)

20:49.541 --> 20:52.000
(song continues,

20:49.541 --> 20:52.000
low and indistinct)

20:54.958 --> 20:56.541
(groans)

20:58.166 --> 21:00.875
(deep, demonic voice):

20:58.166 --> 21:00.875
A shadow older than time falls

21:00.875 --> 21:02.333
over your soul.

21:02.333 --> 21:04.708
You shall be claimed.

21:04.708 --> 21:06.958
Hey, let her go. Come on.

21:04.708 --> 21:06.958
Come on, get off her, man!

21:06.958 --> 21:08.500
(grunts)

21:08.500 --> 21:10.541
Azzaca, what the hell?

21:11.666 --> 21:13.875
Watch yourself, sis.

21:13.875 --> 21:16.000
Your fate has changed.

21:17.208 --> 21:18.208
Protect her.

21:33.375 --> 21:34.666
Mills, where am I?

21:34.666 --> 21:36.291
Somewhere safe.

21:38.291 --> 21:40.458
(handcuffs rattling, clacking)

21:40.458 --> 21:41.791
You can't do this to me.

21:41.791 --> 21:43.958
You need to stay still.

21:43.958 --> 21:45.750
There's something

21:43.958 --> 21:45.750
in your system,

21:45.750 --> 21:48.625
and the more that you struggle,

21:45.750 --> 21:48.625
the faster it'll kill you.

21:48.625 --> 21:50.083
(panting softly)

21:50.083 --> 21:52.166
You'd like that, wouldn't you?

21:52.166 --> 21:53.583
No.

21:53.583 --> 21:55.791
We have people

21:53.583 --> 21:55.791
working on medicine.

21:55.791 --> 21:57.291
You just need to

21:55.791 --> 21:57.291
hang in there.

21:57.291 --> 21:58.666
The roommate?

21:58.666 --> 22:01.208
You trusted me before.

22:01.208 --> 22:04.041
Remember? Right?

22:01.208 --> 22:04.041
Hold on to that, Danny.

22:04.041 --> 22:05.583
(wry chuckle)

22:05.583 --> 22:08.375
You just can't see

22:05.583 --> 22:08.375
what you do to people.

22:10.166 --> 22:14.333
All I can do

22:10.166 --> 22:14.333
is try to do my best,

22:14.333 --> 22:17.083
be a friend, and do

22:14.333 --> 22:17.083
right by you, Danny.

22:17.083 --> 22:19.708
The Outer Banks.

22:19.708 --> 22:22.083
That little shack on the beach.

22:23.583 --> 22:25.916
It wasn't much--

22:23.583 --> 22:25.916
the fan barely moved the air--

22:25.916 --> 22:28.166
but that time...

22:28.166 --> 22:30.875
that you're so hell-bent

22:28.166 --> 22:30.875
on putting in the rearview...

22:30.875 --> 22:33.708
that's when I found you.

22:34.958 --> 22:37.166
That's when I knew.

22:40.000 --> 22:43.333
And you left that place,

22:40.000 --> 22:43.333
but I'm still there.

22:44.916 --> 22:46.708
(knocking on door)

22:54.500 --> 22:58.875
Oh, one who remains hidden...

22:58.875 --> 23:03.833
whose destiny is

22:58.875 --> 23:03.833
to reign over all...

23:03.833 --> 23:07.708
light a pathway to your glory.

23:10.041 --> 23:12.583
The hour of reckoning

23:10.041 --> 23:12.583
draws near.

23:12.583 --> 23:16.250
♪ ♪

23:20.250 --> 23:23.250
An occasion worth celebrating.

23:26.625 --> 23:28.625
♪ ♪

23:32.916 --> 23:33.916
Sister...

23:33.916 --> 23:35.833
(buzzing)

23:35.833 --> 23:37.041
...how do you fare?

23:37.041 --> 23:38.708
(buzzing)

23:44.625 --> 23:46.541
Do you like my dress?

23:46.541 --> 23:49.000
(buzzing)

23:49.000 --> 23:51.166
When a new day dawns

23:49.000 --> 23:51.166
over all that is,

23:51.166 --> 23:53.166
a girl has to look her best.

23:59.875 --> 24:02.791
MAN: It's over on

23:59.875 --> 24:02.791
the other side.

24:02.791 --> 24:05.625
(rock song playing,

24:02.791 --> 24:05.625
low and indistinct)

24:09.000 --> 24:10.875
(sighs)

24:15.416 --> 24:17.833
♪ ...everything she desires... ♪

24:19.666 --> 24:21.666
It's me.

24:23.333 --> 24:26.041
We need to finish this.

24:29.125 --> 24:31.208
The tonic we dosed him with

24:29.125 --> 24:31.208
may keep Danny alive

24:31.208 --> 24:33.833
a little longer, but we need

24:31.208 --> 24:33.833
to get ahead of this thing.

24:33.833 --> 24:36.625
Who knows how many others

24:33.833 --> 24:36.625
have been stung by now?

24:36.625 --> 24:38.666
Grace Dixon's journal

24:36.625 --> 24:38.666
said that Betsy Ross

24:38.666 --> 24:40.625
armed up to go after it.

24:40.625 --> 24:43.750
Yes. The tonic is merely

24:40.625 --> 24:43.750
a stopgap measure.

24:43.750 --> 24:45.500
As long as the

24:43.750 --> 24:45.500
Soucouyant lives,

24:45.500 --> 24:47.708
it shall have a grip

24:45.500 --> 24:47.708
on his soul and...

24:47.708 --> 24:49.625
the fever  will  overcome him.

24:49.625 --> 24:52.125
Fine. How do we kill a swarm?

24:52.125 --> 24:54.791
According to the lore

24:52.125 --> 24:54.791
of the creature,

24:54.791 --> 24:58.083
the Soucouyant can be

24:54.791 --> 24:58.083
destroyed if you...

24:58.083 --> 25:00.125
follow her home

24:58.083 --> 25:00.125
and burn down

25:00.125 --> 25:02.083
her house.

25:00.125 --> 25:02.083
Folklore...

25:02.083 --> 25:03.666
usually has a basis in reality.

25:03.666 --> 25:05.708
What if the answer here isn't

25:05.708 --> 25:07.541
magical in nature

25:05.708 --> 25:07.541
but in the...

25:07.541 --> 25:09.208
behavior

25:07.541 --> 25:09.208
of the insects themselves?

25:09.208 --> 25:10.875
You want to kill bees?

25:10.875 --> 25:13.583
Wasps? Destroy the hive.

25:13.583 --> 25:16.000
They never stray far

25:13.583 --> 25:16.000
from the hive.

25:17.708 --> 25:18.708
Three victims.

25:18.708 --> 25:20.416
Judge...

25:20.416 --> 25:22.208
dedicated to his job--

25:20.416 --> 25:22.208
let's say he was stung

25:22.208 --> 25:23.833
in his chambers. Here.

25:23.833 --> 25:25.708
PTA woman in her house.

25:25.708 --> 25:27.333
Reynolds in his.

25:27.333 --> 25:29.958
We triangulate.

25:29.958 --> 25:32.041
Ah, hold the phone.

25:32.041 --> 25:34.125
Ah. (chuckles)

25:35.333 --> 25:37.583
Wait, wait.

25:41.625 --> 25:42.750
The symbol

25:42.750 --> 25:44.541
on the back of the tablet.

25:47.166 --> 25:48.958
I always thought

25:47.166 --> 25:48.958
it was decorative.

25:49.791 --> 25:50.791
Look...

25:50.791 --> 25:54.333
A tree with six blossoms.

25:54.333 --> 25:57.500
This is the sixth creature

25:54.333 --> 25:57.500
that Pandora has sent.

25:57.500 --> 25:58.791
Whatever it is she's planning,

25:58.791 --> 26:01.000
I fear she may be close

25:58.791 --> 26:01.000
to achieving her goal.

26:01.000 --> 26:02.375
What if the Soucouyant's hive

26:02.375 --> 26:04.125
and Pandora

26:02.375 --> 26:04.125
are in the same place?

26:05.583 --> 26:07.583
CRANE: Then we've found

26:05.583 --> 26:07.583
our enemy's lair.

26:09.166 --> 26:12.125
You sure you're

26:09.166 --> 26:12.125
not hungry?

26:12.125 --> 26:14.666
The chef here makes

26:12.125 --> 26:14.666
a mean Cajun catfish.

26:14.666 --> 26:16.750
Yeah. I've tried it.

26:16.750 --> 26:20.291
My dad used to bring me here

26:16.750 --> 26:20.291
when I was a kid, remember?

26:20.291 --> 26:22.875
Where is your friend?

26:22.875 --> 26:24.041
Mills isn't a part of this.

26:24.041 --> 26:25.666
Hmm.

26:33.083 --> 26:34.875
(chuckles)

26:33.083 --> 26:34.875
Look at us.

26:38.583 --> 26:39.750
So what are these?

26:41.500 --> 26:43.708
Bank accounts? Transit numbers?

26:44.750 --> 26:46.625
That's Liechtenstein

26:44.750 --> 26:46.625
and that's Geneva.

26:46.625 --> 26:48.625
It was your father's idea.

26:46.625 --> 26:48.625
I wanted to hide the cash

26:48.625 --> 26:50.291
in Bolivia, like a...

26:50.291 --> 26:52.041
Butch and Sundance thing.

26:52.041 --> 26:54.208
Back then your father

26:52.041 --> 26:54.208
was much smarter

26:54.208 --> 26:56.000
than me with money.

26:56.000 --> 26:57.583
Congrats on your inheritance.

26:57.583 --> 27:01.250
I mean, even though...

26:57.583 --> 27:01.250
you had to get it by selling out

27:01.250 --> 27:02.291
your friends.

27:03.250 --> 27:04.875
(gun cocks)

27:14.291 --> 27:16.750
Boy, you look like your father,

27:16.750 --> 27:19.666
when we were shavetails

27:16.750 --> 27:19.666
down at Parris Island.

27:21.333 --> 27:24.750
This is where you give me

27:21.333 --> 27:24.750
what I want, son.

27:25.750 --> 27:27.250
That was the arrangement.

27:45.708 --> 27:47.458
What, you think

27:45.708 --> 27:47.458
I'm the villain here?

27:47.458 --> 27:48.541
No, no, no,

27:48.541 --> 27:50.458
it doesn't work

27:48.541 --> 27:50.458
like that.

27:50.458 --> 27:53.666
In this game, son,

27:50.458 --> 27:53.666
the debts collect  you.

27:55.458 --> 27:57.666
Your father learned that

27:55.458 --> 27:57.666
the hard way.

27:57.666 --> 27:59.458
Well, I'm not my father.

27:59.458 --> 28:01.583
Yeah.

28:01.583 --> 28:03.708
Ever asked yourself

28:03.708 --> 28:06.583
why you need to know?

28:06.583 --> 28:07.750
Why we're playing

28:06.583 --> 28:07.750
ring-around-the-rosy

28:07.750 --> 28:09.541
over this little hunk of stone?

28:10.583 --> 28:13.291
You're  exactly  like him.

28:14.750 --> 28:17.583
You're drawn to the darkness,

28:14.750 --> 28:17.583
and you can't look away.

28:18.583 --> 28:19.875
That...

28:19.875 --> 28:23.583
that badge of your father's,

28:19.875 --> 28:23.583
that, uh...

28:23.583 --> 28:26.833
Mayberry sheriff vibe...

28:26.833 --> 28:29.416
that was not

28:26.833 --> 28:29.416
August Corbin.

28:29.416 --> 28:31.666
No, he knew the truth.

28:31.666 --> 28:33.625
There is no good...

28:33.625 --> 28:35.833
no evil...

28:35.833 --> 28:38.041
just...

28:40.166 --> 28:41.166
(click)

28:45.333 --> 28:47.125
(eerie whooshing)

28:49.583 --> 28:51.583
...power.

28:59.958 --> 29:01.083
All right,

28:59.958 --> 29:01.083
let's go for a ride.

29:01.958 --> 29:03.458
Hey. Hey!

29:03.458 --> 29:04.583
Hey!

29:10.791 --> 29:12.208
Call off your dogs.

29:16.041 --> 29:16.875
Guns.

29:22.958 --> 29:24.250
The Shard.

29:24.250 --> 29:26.416
You're making a big mistake.

29:26.416 --> 29:28.375
That's my specialty.

29:28.375 --> 29:29.416
Jacket pocket.

29:39.583 --> 29:40.583
Move.

29:50.625 --> 29:52.958
He said the numbers were

29:50.625 --> 29:52.958
for Swiss bank accounts.

29:52.958 --> 29:55.416
If there's money...

29:52.958 --> 29:55.416
my dad's money.

29:55.416 --> 29:56.416
You believe him?

29:56.416 --> 29:57.583
I don't know.

29:57.583 --> 29:59.416
Well, we got more than

29:57.583 --> 29:59.416
we could've hoped for.

30:00.458 --> 30:01.833
(whoosh)

30:05.958 --> 30:06.958
Go!

30:06.958 --> 30:08.833
Go!

30:06.958 --> 30:08.833
(engine revs)

30:20.250 --> 30:23.583
These ruins are ancient.

30:23.583 --> 30:25.958
The architecture...

30:25.958 --> 30:27.958
unlike anything

30:25.958 --> 30:27.958
I've ever seen.

30:33.083 --> 30:37.541
(buzzing)

30:43.125 --> 30:45.500
I hate it when you're right.

30:51.583 --> 30:53.625
Whoa. Find the hive.

30:51.583 --> 30:53.625
I'll buy us some time.

30:53.625 --> 30:54.833
All right.

30:54.833 --> 30:57.333
Okay... hey...

30:57.333 --> 30:59.791
Secrets.

31:02.666 --> 31:04.958
Chaos.

31:07.916 --> 31:10.375
Loneliness.

31:13.708 --> 31:15.666
Innocence lost.

31:15.666 --> 31:17.166
Death.

31:22.583 --> 31:24.708
And the last little one...

31:24.708 --> 31:26.583
CRANE:

31:24.708 --> 31:26.583
Fear itself.

31:32.166 --> 31:36.083
The tree, the flowers,

31:36.083 --> 31:38.625
the creatures you summoned,

31:36.083 --> 31:38.625
they all serve a single purpose,

31:38.625 --> 31:39.750
do they not?

31:39.750 --> 31:41.750
You're cultivating

31:41.750 --> 31:43.041
forms of terror.

31:43.041 --> 31:45.208
Very specific ones.

31:45.208 --> 31:47.208
And I should

31:45.208 --> 31:47.208
thank you

31:47.208 --> 31:48.750
and your lady friend

31:48.750 --> 31:51.083
for cleaning up

31:48.750 --> 31:51.083
behind me.

31:51.083 --> 31:54.500
Calling beasts out of the box

31:51.083 --> 31:54.500
was quite easy.

31:54.500 --> 31:57.166
You did all the hard work.

31:57.166 --> 31:58.583
It ends now.

31:58.583 --> 32:00.750
As all good things must.

32:00.750 --> 32:03.000
(buzzing)

32:20.291 --> 32:22.583
I know what it feels like,

32:22.583 --> 32:25.083
to be in the presence

32:22.583 --> 32:25.083
of someone

32:25.083 --> 32:27.041
much greater than myself.

32:27.041 --> 32:28.666
I've seen this tree before.

32:29.833 --> 32:32.166
I have an ancient tablet.

32:32.166 --> 32:34.000
I'd like to give you

32:32.166 --> 32:34.000
a history lesson.

32:34.000 --> 32:35.833
Not another step.

32:34.000 --> 32:35.833
If I didn't already have

32:35.833 --> 32:37.583
all the fear I need,

32:37.583 --> 32:38.583
I'd make this

32:38.583 --> 32:39.541
last a little longer...

32:44.625 --> 32:46.666
(buzzing)

32:59.541 --> 33:02.083
No time to play.

33:03.500 --> 33:06.708
ABBIE:

33:03.500 --> 33:06.708
Crane?

33:08.125 --> 33:09.333
(Crane grunts)

33:10.750 --> 33:12.916
Gone for now.

33:10.750 --> 33:12.916
Could be back any moment.

33:12.916 --> 33:14.125
Bigger problems.

33:14.125 --> 33:15.750
Whatever Pandora has planned,

33:15.750 --> 33:17.833
I fear it is coming to fruition

33:15.750 --> 33:17.833
as we speak.

33:17.833 --> 33:19.458
(deep rumbling)

33:19.458 --> 33:20.708
The hive.

33:20.708 --> 33:22.625
Middle of the lair,

33:20.708 --> 33:22.625
above the pool.

33:22.625 --> 33:25.541
We start with that, then the

33:22.625 --> 33:25.541
bitch with the box. You got 'em?

33:25.541 --> 33:26.458
Yes.

33:26.458 --> 33:27.708
Greek fire, eh?

33:27.708 --> 33:29.666
No. We used all that

33:27.708 --> 33:29.666
burning General Howe.

33:29.666 --> 33:31.291
That's prussic acid.

33:31.291 --> 33:32.541
Very unstable.

33:32.541 --> 33:33.750
Right now, so am I.

33:37.666 --> 33:39.541
Be wary.

33:41.541 --> 33:43.125
(buzzing)

33:55.791 --> 33:57.375
(buzzing)

34:07.958 --> 34:10.583
(grunting)

34:16.375 --> 34:17.583
(shouts)

34:17.583 --> 34:18.750
(buzzing)

34:21.583 --> 34:22.583
(groans loudly)

34:31.250 --> 34:33.416
(screeching)

34:37.625 --> 34:38.750
Aah!

34:44.375 --> 34:46.625
(panting)

34:52.458 --> 34:54.708
♪ ♪

35:02.541 --> 35:04.166
Bear witness.

35:04.166 --> 35:06.166
(crackling)

35:08.583 --> 35:09.583
Stop!

35:31.083 --> 35:32.583
(monitor beeping,

35:31.083 --> 35:32.583
Reynolds groans quietly)

35:32.583 --> 35:33.875
WOMAN (over P.A.):

35:32.583 --> 35:33.875
Dr. Harris to O.R., please.

35:33.875 --> 35:35.625
Dr. Harris to O.R.,

35:33.875 --> 35:35.625
please.

35:38.791 --> 35:41.333
Abs?

35:41.333 --> 35:43.750
How are you feeling?

35:43.750 --> 35:45.583
Last thing I remember

35:45.583 --> 35:47.875
was the crime scene.

35:47.875 --> 35:49.708
Yeah?

35:51.250 --> 35:53.250
Well, that was hours ago.

35:53.250 --> 35:57.375
Some kind of messed-up

35:53.250 --> 35:57.375
bug bite took you down.

35:57.375 --> 35:59.875
You had a major

35:57.375 --> 35:59.875
allergic reaction.

35:59.875 --> 36:02.041
Somehow we got you to

35:59.875 --> 36:02.041
the hospital in time,

36:02.041 --> 36:03.625
pumped you full

36:02.041 --> 36:03.625
of antihistamines,

36:03.625 --> 36:05.250
and you've been out cold since.

36:05.250 --> 36:07.791
I was pretty out of it, huh?

36:07.791 --> 36:09.625
Mm-hmm.

36:09.625 --> 36:11.125
Talking nonsense?

36:11.125 --> 36:12.625
No more than usual.

36:12.625 --> 36:14.625
(both laugh)

36:14.625 --> 36:16.291
That bad, huh?

36:16.291 --> 36:18.416
Yeah.

36:18.416 --> 36:20.708
You'd tell me, right?

36:20.708 --> 36:23.708
Nothing I didn't already know.

36:23.708 --> 36:26.416
Hey.

36:26.416 --> 36:28.375
Rest up.

36:28.375 --> 36:29.916
We need you back

36:28.375 --> 36:29.916
running the show.

36:33.750 --> 36:35.791
Abbie...

36:35.791 --> 36:38.583
I get the impression

36:35.791 --> 36:38.583
I'm still kickin' 'cause of you.

36:38.583 --> 36:40.208
I try.

36:41.583 --> 36:44.625
Always will.

36:47.708 --> 36:50.166
♪ ♪

36:54.416 --> 36:57.416
Miss Corinth.

36:57.416 --> 37:00.125
Oh!

37:00.125 --> 37:01.625
Oh!

37:01.625 --> 37:03.125
(chuckles)

37:01.625 --> 37:03.125
Uh...

37:01.625 --> 37:03.125
(chuckles)

37:03.125 --> 37:05.333
Thank you.

37:03.125 --> 37:05.333
Well... thank you.

37:05.333 --> 37:07.333
They're beautiful.

37:05.333 --> 37:07.333
Delightful.

37:07.333 --> 37:10.750
Uh, so... what's the plan?

37:10.750 --> 37:12.333
Oh, there isn't one.

37:12.333 --> 37:14.333
No plan, no agenda.

37:14.333 --> 37:16.791
No Internet in days.

37:16.791 --> 37:18.041
I like it.

37:18.041 --> 37:20.041
Despite my fears

37:20.041 --> 37:22.041
that you may find

37:20.041 --> 37:22.041
my predilections

37:22.041 --> 37:24.416
somewhat old-fashioned,

37:24.416 --> 37:27.666
the truth is I rather

37:24.416 --> 37:27.666
enjoy a constitutional.

37:27.666 --> 37:29.666
No destination in mind.

37:29.666 --> 37:32.666
Simply... a wander.

37:32.666 --> 37:35.208
So no rezzy at Le Cirque?

37:35.208 --> 37:37.583
No hot stone massage

37:35.208 --> 37:37.583
for two? 3-D IMAX?

37:37.583 --> 37:41.041
Hot air balloon

37:37.583 --> 37:41.041
to a wine tasting?

37:37.583 --> 37:41.041
No.

37:41.041 --> 37:42.625
A walk.

37:42.625 --> 37:45.458
Mr. Ichabod Crane...

37:45.458 --> 37:47.250
are you inviting me

37:45.458 --> 37:47.250
to join you

37:47.250 --> 37:49.375
on a turn

37:47.250 --> 37:49.375
of this lovely meadow?

37:49.375 --> 37:52.583
Usually I make the circuit

37:49.375 --> 37:52.583
alone with my thoughts,

37:52.583 --> 37:54.416
but...

37:54.416 --> 37:56.083
times are changing.

37:56.083 --> 37:57.916
And so must I.

38:01.916 --> 38:04.208
This is

38:01.916 --> 38:04.208
the official first date.

38:04.208 --> 38:06.708
Mm, technically our second.

38:06.708 --> 38:07.791
Just go with it.

38:16.541 --> 38:18.291
ABBIE:

38:16.541 --> 38:18.291
From the blank look

38:16.541 --> 38:18.291
on your face,

38:18.291 --> 38:20.083
I take it your

38:18.291 --> 38:20.083
date went well.

38:20.083 --> 38:22.500
(clears throat)

38:20.083 --> 38:22.500
I cannot recall

38:22.500 --> 38:26.750
which great, great Colonial

38:22.500 --> 38:26.750
thinker coined the phrase

38:26.750 --> 38:30.250
"'Twas a tiny patch

38:26.750 --> 38:30.250
of paradise."

38:30.250 --> 38:32.875
Oh, no, wait, it was me.

38:32.875 --> 38:35.333
A wise woman once said,

38:32.875 --> 38:35.333
"Don't get ahead of yourself."

38:36.416 --> 38:37.750
Oh, wait.

38:37.750 --> 38:39.500
That was every woman.

38:39.500 --> 38:40.625
Point taken.

38:42.375 --> 38:44.583
How does Agent Reynolds fare?

38:44.583 --> 38:46.791
He'll make a full recovery,

38:46.791 --> 38:48.541
and... thankfully,

38:48.541 --> 38:50.708
he doesn't remember anything,

38:48.541 --> 38:50.708
which is a blessing

38:50.708 --> 38:52.125
on so many levels.

38:52.125 --> 38:53.125
Uh...

38:53.125 --> 38:54.916
I'm trying to figure out

38:54.916 --> 38:57.041
where Pandora

38:54.916 --> 38:57.041
may have gone.

38:57.041 --> 38:58.666
That passage

38:58.666 --> 39:01.666
under the tree,

38:58.666 --> 39:01.666
the stairwell leading down...

39:01.666 --> 39:06.166
Trees are often associated with

39:01.666 --> 39:06.166
the entrance to the underworld.

39:06.166 --> 39:09.250
Yggdrasil,

39:06.166 --> 39:09.250
the Norse realm of Hel.

39:09.250 --> 39:10.833
The levels

39:09.250 --> 39:10.833
of Dante's  Inferno

39:10.833 --> 39:13.666
can be interpreted

39:10.833 --> 39:13.666
as a stairwell of sorts.

39:10.833 --> 39:13.666
Yeah,

39:13.666 --> 39:14.541
that sounds like good news.

39:16.083 --> 39:17.666
You're thinking

39:16.083 --> 39:17.666
that everything up until now

39:17.666 --> 39:19.083
has been a warm-up act.

39:20.375 --> 39:23.291
I'd stake my life on it.

39:23.291 --> 39:24.791
The tree,

39:24.791 --> 39:26.875
the types of fear she raised--

39:26.875 --> 39:29.166
she's preparing something.

39:29.166 --> 39:32.833
I fear her return

39:29.166 --> 39:32.833
is inevitable.

39:32.833 --> 39:35.625
The only question is...

39:35.625 --> 39:39.250
what insidious plan

39:35.625 --> 39:39.250
does she have for her return?

39:39.250 --> 39:41.500
Whatever it is,

39:41.500 --> 39:44.083
she messed with our town,

39:44.083 --> 39:46.166
our friends,

39:46.166 --> 39:49.458
and the people

39:46.166 --> 39:49.458
that we care about.

39:49.458 --> 39:51.708
If she wants a rematch,

39:49.458 --> 39:51.708
I say bring it on.

39:51.708 --> 39:54.041
Oh, Lieutenant,

39:54.041 --> 39:56.375
that is a quote we can live by.

40:02.166 --> 40:05.125
(thunder rumbling)

40:05.125 --> 40:06.375
(grunting quietly)

40:07.583 --> 40:09.083
(grunting)

40:13.625 --> 40:16.166
(overlapping, indistinct voices)

40:27.458 --> 40:30.250
(gasping, panting)

